data.title: NO LONGER OPENED
data.text: This great restaurant has been closed for awhile now.  It's sad!  It was featured on Food Network. It served the community well.

data.title: Only if you want a burger
data.text: Okay, I really hate to rate something poor if it's clean, the service is decent, yada yada.  I went with five girlfriends and the only ones happy ordered hamburgers which to me were greasy looking.  I  will admit that the french fries were good though.  My salad was wilted and I didn't like the dressing. Most of the place seems to be a bar to me. And perhaps they should stay with serving drinks and burgers.  They also have craft beers which I can't vouch for. Won't be going back.

data.title: Great little spot!
data.text: Located in Oxnard, this restaurant was put on the map a few years ago by Guy Fieri when featured on the food network.  The atmosphere is quaint and the food was delicious!  I had the Cuban and the garlic fries as recommended by the server.

data.title: Great burger and fries!
data.text:
We decided to try the Kitchen after hearing about it through the Oxnard Dine and Discover week. The restaurant is in downtown Oxnard and was mostly empty during the lunch hour. It's mostly a bar and we're guessing that it's hopping in the evenings and on the weekend.
We tried the burger special - a sirloin burger topped with guacamole, sauteed onions, mushrooms, pepper jack cheese, and chipotle aoili sauce. We ordered it medium rare and it was cooked perfectly. The burger was delicious - moist, flavorful and plenty big enough for us to share.
We also shared the salad special which was a crispy chipotle-seasoned chicken breast with field greens and assorted other items. The chicken was not prepared to order so it was cold and tough. The salad would have been really good had the chicken been cooked to order.
We will try the Kitchen again to check out some of their other menu items including Fish & Chips and perhaps the salmon. 

Overall, we recommend the Kitchen although we found it a bit pricey for what we ordered.

data.title: Blah
data.text: They may have been on Guy Fieri's show but I am not impressed. He definitely missed the mark on this place. Like the last person said bad food and bad service. No flavor.

data.title: POOR Service, POOR Food
data.text: I never write poor reviews, but I felt compelled to do so, so others do not have to go through what we did.  We tried this place with friends from work on a Friday.  The place was relatively slow although the service was as if it was jamb packed.  We asked for water for all and did not get it for 45-60 minutes.  Every time we asked for something it would be 20+ minutes before the waitress acted on it and although I could give her some leeway, the number of errors and mis-orders were so many that I got tired of hearing "I'm so sorry".  We received our dinner  about an hour and a half after we got there and the food was cold and bland.  We were told the cook did not get 2 of our orders and they had to wait even longer to get their food.  Overall, the experience was awful although made bearable with the good company of my work friends.

data.title: Great mussels
data.text: I was intrigued with the menu so decided to try this place.  I had a sangria and the mussels. Both were quite good. Service friendly and good. Place a little dark.

data.title: Celebrated my one son's birthday
data.text: The atmosphere was average as we sat right alongside the bar.  I feel this restaurant should use the very large room at the front and set up tables, but for some reason since they opened they've chosen to leave that space vacant.  They could have much more business if that was used and with linen tablecloths rather than white butcher paper style used in the bar area.  I love their Asian chicken wrap and that is what I had.  My son had one of their specialty burgers.  I had hoped for something a little more fancy for his birthday but he seemed content.  The food was tasty and the waiter was fine.  Mu son and I both chose their onion rings in panko crumbs and a really ample amount came as the side order.

data.title: Great restaurant
data.text: Excellent food an service.  In historic area of Oxnard.  Good menu and selection of beer.  Busy at lunch time, so go early or after the lunch crowd.

data.title: Oh
data.text: Not a place that I would take children. Well, at least not my children. Not impressed by location, cleanliness, nor the food. Maybe just not my style.

data.title: Greasy floors with great sandwich
data.text: We were hesitant to give this place a try.  You nearly slide coming in the door because the floors are coated with grease.  We had the Cuban sandwich and it was quite tasty.  The server was friendly, but very slow. The booths were cozy, but need a cleaning too.

data.title: We've been there a couple times....
data.text: We haven't had a bad meal yet. Very nice pub and the service has been great. We've tried a few dishes we've never had before and were very pleased. Mark was our serve and was very attentive. Recommendations for the beer was spot on!! Will definitely be back...

data.title: Happy Hour is the Time to Try Out This Restaurant
data.text:
We thought the Kitchen was suppose to be a Mexican restaurant and bakery. Actually it is a bar that serves food. However, they do advertise a banquet  room and dinning room. We saw neither but this place is very deceiving. It is difficult to find the front door with signs on three sides of the building it is housed in leading you to the door. It is dark inside but it has a long bar with comfortable booths along the wall. Restroom is clean although my shoes stuck to the floor with each step.

They have a great beer selection and you can get a flight of beers, six in all, in either 5 or 10 oz glasses. The specialty beers are not poured at the bar but rather in a back room...a little strange. The beers we chose were very good.

The menu is very limited and the prices are a little steep for this establishment. We shared a Cuban sandwich which was very good served on home made bread with parmesan garlic fries.

Our waitress, Stephanie was terrific. She was very patient, helpful in answering our questions and extremely friendly.

They have a happy hour M-F from 3-6 where side dishes and beer is discounted. If I ever return and I doubt I will, I would go for the happy hour.

data.title: Would you like a lot of salt with your meal?
data.text: The ambiance isn't there but we wanted to try a new restaurant locally.  The salmon was over cooked and salted within an inch of it's life, so was the garlic rice, without garlic.  The presentation was wonderful, if only the taste went with it.  Not a second chance there.

data.title: Just an average night here....
data.text:
Been a semi regular customer here.....has its ups and downs...
Recent visit wasn't really impressed....and (not their fault) a few
patrons looked like trouble....as they were schnockered at the bar!
Place has really good beer selections....food choices haven't changed
much so kinda disinterested.....

data.title: Almost Hidden
data.text: In the heart of downtown but almost hidden off large parking lot facing the plaza. A big cut above and definitely shows creativity in what otherwise might be standard midday fare. Atmospheric wooden booths, paneling, bar. High quality groceries and prep.

data.title: Yummy and cheesy!
data.text: Visited for lunch with two friends. Started with the mac n cheese appetizer - very cheesy and delicious. Two of us ordered the grilled cheese w/bacon sandwich. A good balance of cheese, tomatoes, bacon and basil. The bread was outstanding. Our other guest ordered the pesto/veggie sandwich and ate every bite! The service was just fine, very attentive and well-paced. We will definitely go back.

data.title: Hidden gem in Oxnard
data.text:
What a hidden gem this turned out to be.  We found it by trying places in the Ventura Axxess card.

With so many chain restaurants out there it's nice to have a Mom and Pop restaurant in Oxnard that serves such terrific food.

We were there for dinner.  We got a few appetizers (fried green beans & the artichoke) and also the salmon dinner and vegetable stack.  Everything was terrific.  The fried green beans were the best we have ever tasted.  

Fresh ingredients and great presentation.  

Good selection of beer.  The prices were very good for everything.  

Our server was wonderful.  Very attentive.  The entire staff was outstanding.  The owner came over and talked to us for a while.  She was super friendly.  

Can't wait to go back and try the burgers.  We saw some being delivered to other diners and they looked fantastic.  

We will definitely be back!!!!

data.title: Tasty food and brews in a decent downtown setting.
data.text: Dropped in for dinner on blues night and the music was great!  Service was excellent and prices are right on. Fried green beans were better than any we've had in the South!!  Would return for sure.

data.title: Nothing Special
data.text: Went to this place a couple times with friends. Food is below average diner style food. Doesn't come out all that hot. Service is a little slow and the guy bussing and bringing drinks dresses and talks in a street like manner. I guess the place was on DDD. Doesn't mean it's good.
